msgid "*28.1*\tWhat is folding?\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:32
msgid ""
"Folding is used to show a range of lines in the buffer as a single line on "
"the screen.  Like a piece of paper which is folded to make it shorter:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:46
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t+------------------------+\n"
"\t| line 1\t\t |\n"
"\t| line 2\t\t |\n"
"\t| line 3\t\t |\n"
"\t|_______________________ |\n"
"\t\\\t\t\t \\\n"
"\t \\________________________\\\n"
"\t / folded lines\t\t  /\n"
"\t/________________________/\n"
"\t| line 12\t\t |\n"
"\t| line 13\t\t |\n"
"\t| line 14\t\t |\n"
"\t+------------------------+\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:49
msgid ""
"The text is still in the buffer, unchanged.  Only the way lines are "
"displayed is affected by folding."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:53
msgid ""
"The advantage of folding is that you can get a better overview of the "
"structure of text, by folding lines of a section and replacing it with a "
"line that indicates that there is a section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "*28.2*\tManual folding\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:58
msgid "Try it out: Position the cursor in a paragraph and type: >"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:60
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\t\"fp\n"
msgid "\tzfap\n"
msgstr "\t\"fp\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:65
msgid ""
"You will see that the paragraph is replaced by a highlighted line.  You have "
"created a fold.  |zf| is an operator and |ap| a text object selection.  You "
"can use the |zf| operator with any movement command to create a fold for the "
"text that it moved over.  |zf| also works in Visual mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:67
msgid "To view the text again, open the fold by typing: >"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:69
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\tdo\n"
msgid "\tzo\n"
msgstr "\tdo\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:71
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "And what you want is the following:"
msgid "And you can close the fold again with: >"
msgstr "Y lo que quiere es lo siguiente:"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:73
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\t]c\n"
msgid "\tzc\n"
