#| msgid "*22.3*\tFinding a file\n"
msgid "*28.5*\tFolding by indent\n"
msgstr "*22.3*\tEncontrar un archivo\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:219
msgid ""
"Defining folds with |zf| is a lot of work.  If your text is structured by "
"giving lower level items a larger indent, you can use the indent folding "
"method.  This will create folds for every sequence of lines with the same "
"indent.  Lines with a larger indent will become nested folds.  This works "
"well with many programming languages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:221
msgid "Try this by setting the 'foldmethod' option: >"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:223
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\t:set autoindent\n"
msgid "\t:set foldmethod=indent\n"
msgstr "\t:set autoindent\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:226
msgid ""
"Then you can use the |zm| and |zr| commands to fold more and reduce "
"folding.  It's easy to see on this example text:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This line is not indented\n"
"\tThis line is indented once\n"
"\t\tThis line is indented twice\n"
"\t\tThis line is indented twice\n"
"\tThis line is indented once\n"
"This line is not indented\n"
"\tThis line is indented once\n"
"\tThis line is indented once\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:239
msgid ""
"Note that the relation between the amount of indent and the fold depth "
"depends on the 'shiftwidth' option.  Each 'shiftwidth' worth of indent adds "
"one to the depth of the fold.  This is called a fold level."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:242
msgid ""
"When you use the |zr| and |zm| commands you actually increase or decrease "
"the 'foldlevel' option.  You could also set it directly: >"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:244
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "\t:set modelines=10\n"
msgid "\t:set foldlevel=3\n"
msgstr "\t:set modelines=10\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:250
msgid ""
"This means that all folds with three times a 'shiftwidth' indent or more "
"will be closed.  The lower the foldlevel, the more folds will be closed.  "
"When 'foldlevel' is zero, all folds are closed.  |zM| does set 'foldlevel' "
"to zero.  The opposite command |zR| sets 'foldlevel' to the deepest fold "
"level that is present in the file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Thus there are two ways to open and close the folds:\n"
"(A) By setting the fold level.\n"
"    This gives a very quick way of \"zooming out\" to view the structure of the\n"
"    text, move the cursor, and \"zoom in\" on the text again.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:259
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(B) By using |zo| and |zc| commands to open or close specific folds.\n"
"    This allows opening only those folds that you want to be open, while other\n"
"    folds remain closed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:263
msgid ""
"This can be combined: You can first close most folds by using |zm| a few "
"times and then open a specific fold with |zo|.  Or open all folds with |zR| "
"and then close specific folds with |zc|."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:266
msgid ""
"But you cannot manually define folds when 'foldmethod' is \"indent\", as "
"that would conflict with the relation between the indent and the fold level."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:268
msgid "More about folding by indent in the reference manual: |fold-indent|"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:271
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
