#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:391
#, no-wrap
msgid "*28.10* Which fold method to use?\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:394
msgid ""
"All these possibilities make you wonder which method you should chose.  "
"Unfortunately, there is no golden rule.  Here are some hints."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:399
msgid ""
"If there is a syntax file with folding for the language you are editing, "
"that is probably the best choice.  If there isn't one, you might try to "
"write it.  This requires a good knowledge of search patterns.  It's not "
"easy, but when it's working you will not have to define folds manually."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:402
msgid ""
"Typing commands to manually fold regions can be used for unstructured text.  "
"Then use the |:mkview| command to save and restore your folds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:409
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The marker method requires you to change the file.  If you are sharing the\n"
"files with other people or you have to meet company standards, you might not\n"
"be allowed to add them.\n"
"   The main advantage of markers is that you can put them exactly where you\n"
"want them.  That avoids that a few lines are missed when you cut and paste\n"
"folds.  And you can add a comment about what is contained in the fold.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:414
msgid ""
"Folding by indent is something that works in many files, but not always very "
"well.  Use it when you can't use one of the other methods.  However, it is "
"very useful for outlining.  Then you specifically use one 'shiftwidth' for "
"each nesting level."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original/TXT/usr_28.txt:421
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Folding with expressions can make folds in almost any structured text.  It is\n"
"quite simple to specify, especially if the start and end of a fold can easily\n"
"be recognized.\n"
"   If you use the \"expr\" method to define folds, but they are not exactly how\n"
"you want them, you could switch to the \"manual\" method.  This will not remove\n"
"the defined folds.  Then you can delete or add folds manually.\n"
msgstr ""

